Hey <%= @user.first_name_or_fallback %>,

Read-only MCP access was just enabled for your Dabble Me account (<%= @user.email %>). If you turned this on, you can ignore this message.

MCP connections use a separate secret token (shown only once when you generate it) and expire after six months unless you generate a new token. For Claude custom connectors, paste the full URL from your MCP settings page (it includes access_token= in the query string).

If you did not enable MCP, sign in and revoke access from your MCP settings page:
<%= new_user_session_url %>
<%= settings_mcp_url %>

Thanks,
Dabble Me
